<section class="program-content">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="program-content__grid">
      <div class="program-content__main">
        <div class="program-content__section">
          <h2 class="program-content__heading font-display">What It Is</h2>
          <p>SEAT is an eight-week intensive that prepares young people to serve on civic boards, advisory councils, commissions, and community decision-making bodies. Not someday. Now.</p>
          <p>Participants learn how local government actually works&mdash;budgets, agendas, Robert&rsquo;s Rules, public testimony&mdash;then get matched with real civic placement opportunities in the DFW region.</p>
          <p>By the end, every SEAT participant has applied to or been placed on at least one civic body. The goal is not training. The goal is a seat.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="program-content__section">
          <h2 class="program-content__heading font-display">Eight Weeks. One Seat.</h2>
          <p>Each week targets a specific skill: civic mapping, public speaking, policy analysis, board dynamics, stakeholder engagement, application strategy, interview preparation, and placement support.</p>
          <p>Sessions are led by current and former board members, council appointees, and civic leaders who got their start young.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="program-content__aside">
